Phase\-vocoder CLI for multi\-file, multi\-channel time stretching and pitch shifting.

positional arguments:
  inputs                Input audio files/globs or '\-' for stdin

options:
  \-h, \-\-help            show this help message and exit

I/O:
  \-o, \-\-output\-dir OUTPUT_DIR
                        Directory for output files (default: same directory as each input)
  \-\-suffix SUFFIX       Suffix appended to output filename stem (default: _pv)
  \-\-output\-format OUTPUT_FORMAT
                        Output format/extension (e.g. wav, flac, aiff). Default: keep input extension.
  \-\-out, \-\-output OUTPUT
                        Explicit output file path (single\-input mode only). Alias: \-\-out
  \-\-overwrite           Overwrite existing outputs
  \-\-dry\-run             Resolve settings without writing files
  \-\-stdout              Write processed audio to stdout stream (for piping); requires exactly one input

Debug:
  \-\-verbosity {silent,quiet,normal,verbose,debug}
                        Console verbosity level
  \-v, \-\-verbose         Increase verbosity (repeat for extra detail)
  \-\-quiet               Reduce output and hide status bars
  \-\-silent              Suppress all console output
  \-\-explain\-plan        Print resolved processing plan JSON and exit without rendering audio.

Beginner experience:
  \-\-preset {none,default,vocal,ambient,extreme,vocal_studio,drums_safe,extreme_ambient,stereo_coherent}
                        High\-level intent preset. Legacy: none/vocal/ambient/extreme. New: default/vocal_studio/drums_safe/extreme_ambient/stereo_coherent.
  \-\-example {all,basic,vocal,ambient,extreme,drums_safe,stereo_coherent,hybrid,benchmark,gpu,pipeline,csv}
                        Print copy\-paste example command(s) and exit.
  \-\-guided              Interactive guided mode for first\-time users.
  \-\-stretch STRETCH     Alias for \-\-time\-stretch. Accepts scalar or control file (.csv/.json).
  \-\-gpu                 Alias for \-\-device cuda.
  \-\-cpu                 Alias for \-\-device cpu.

Performance:
  \-\-quality\-profile {neutral,speech,music,percussion,ambient,extreme}
                        Named tuning profile for vocoder defaults (default: neutral)
  \-\-auto\-profile        Analyze input and choose a profile automatically (speech/music/percussion/ambient/extreme).
  \-\-auto\-profile\-lookahead\-seconds AUTO_PROFILE_LOOKAHEAD_SECONDS
                        Seconds of audio used when estimating \-\-auto\-profile (default: 6.0).
  \-\-auto\-transform      Allow automatic transform selection when \-\-transform is not explicitly set.

Quality/Phase:
  \-\-n\-fft N_FFT         FFT size (default: 2048). Accepts scalar or control file (.csv/.json).
  \-\-win\-length WIN_LENGTH
                        Window length in samples (default: 2048). Accepts scalar or control file (.csv/.json).
  \-\-hop\-size HOP_SIZE   Hop size in samples (default: 512). Accepts scalar or control file (.csv/.json).
  \-\-window {hann,hamming,blackman,blackmanharris,nuttall,flattop,blackman_nuttall,exact_blackman,sine,bartlett,boxcar,triangular,bartlett_hann,tukey,tukey_0p1,tukey_0p25,tukey_0p75,tukey_0p9,parzen,lanczos,welch,gaussian_0p25,gaussian_0p35,gaussian_0p45,gaussian_0p55,gaussian_0p65,general_gaussian_1p5_0p35,general_gaussian_2p0_0p35,general_gaussian_3p0_0p35,general_gaussian_4p0_0p35,exponential_0p25,exponential_0p5,exponential_1p0,cauchy_0p5,cauchy_1p0,cauchy_2p0,cosine_power_2,cosine_power_3,cosine_power_4,hann_poisson_0p5,hann_poisson_1p0,hann_poisson_2p0,general_hamming_0p50,general_hamming_0p60,general_hamming_0p70,general_hamming_0p80,bohman,cosine,kaiser,rect}
                        Window type (default: hann)
  \-\-kaiser\-beta KAISER_BETA
                        Kaiser window beta parameter used when \-\-window kaiser (default: 14.0). Accepts scalar or control file (.csv/.json).
  \-\-transform {fft,dft,czt,dct,dst,hartley}
                        Per\-frame transform backend for STFT/ISTFT paths (default: fft; options: fft, dft, czt, dct, dst, hartley)
  \-\-no\-center           Disable center padding in STFT/ISTFT
  \-\-phase\-locking {off,identity}
                        Inter\-bin phase locking mode for transient fidelity (default: identity)
  \-\-phase\-engine {propagate,hybrid,random}
                        Phase synthesis engine: propagate (classic phase vocoder), hybrid (propagated + stochastic blend), random (ambient stochastic phase).
  \-\-ambient\-phase\-mix AMBIENT_PHASE_MIX
                        Random\-phase blend when \-\-phase\-engine hybrid (0.0=propagated only, 1.0=random only; default: 0.5). Accepts scalar or control file (.csv/.json).
  \-\-phase\-random\-seed PHASE_RANDOM_SEED
                        Optional deterministic seed for random/hybrid phase generation.
  \-\-transient\-preserve  Enable transient phase resets based on spectral flux
  \-\-transient\-threshold TRANSIENT_THRESHOLD
                        Spectral\-flux multiplier for transient detection (default: 2.0). Accepts scalar or control file (.csv/.json).
  \-\-fourier\-sync        Enable fundamental frame locking. Uses generic short\-time Fourier transforms with per\-frame FFT sizes locked to detected F0.
  \-\-fourier\-sync\-min\-fft FOURIER_SYNC_MIN_FFT
                        Minimum frame FFT size for \-\-fourier\-sync (default: 256). Accepts scalar or control file (.csv/.json).
  \-\-fourier\-sync\-max\-fft FOURIER_SYNC_MAX_FFT
                        Maximum frame FFT size for \-\-fourier\-sync (default: 8192). Accepts scalar or control file (.csv/.json).
  \-\-fourier\-sync\-smooth FOURIER_SYNC_SMOOTH
                        Smoothing span (frames) for prescanned F0 track in \-\-fourier\-sync (default: 5). Accepts scalar or control file (.csv/.json).
  \-\-multires\-fusion     Blend multiple FFT resolutions for each channel before pitch resampling.
  \-\-multires\-ffts MULTIRES_FFTS
                        Comma\-separated FFT sizes for \-\-multires\-fusion (default: 1024,2048,4096)
  \-\-multires\-weights MULTIRES_WEIGHTS
                        Comma\-separated fusion weights for \-\-multires\-fusion (defaults to equal weights).
  \-\-device {auto,cpu,cuda}
                        Compute device: auto (prefer CUDA), cpu, or cuda
  \-\-cuda\-device CUDA_DEVICE
                        CUDA device index used when \-\-device is auto/cuda (default: 0)

Time/Pitch:
  \-\-time\-stretch, \-\-time\-stretch\-factor TIME_STRETCH
                        Final duration multiplier (1.0=unchanged, 2.0=2x longer). Accepts scalar or control file (.csv/.json).
  \-\-target\-duration TARGET_DURATION
                        Absolute target duration in seconds (overrides \-\-time\-stretch)
  \-\-stretch\-mode {auto,standard,multistage}
                        Stretch strategy: standard (single pass), multistage (chained moderate passes), or auto (multistage only for extreme ratios; default: auto).
  \-\-extreme\-time\-stretch
                        Force multistage strategy even when ratio is moderate.
  \-\-extreme\-stretch\-threshold EXTREME_STRETCH_THRESHOLD
                        Auto\-mode threshold for multistage activation (default: 2.0). Accepts scalar or control file (.csv/.json).
  \-\-max\-stage\-stretch MAX_STAGE_STRETCH
                        Maximum per\-stage ratio used in multistage mode (default: 1.8). Accepts scalar or control file (.csv/.json).
  \-\-onset\-time\-credit   Enable onset\-triggered time\-credit scheduling to reduce transient smear during extreme stretching.
  \-\-onset\-credit\-pull ONSET_CREDIT_PULL
                        Fraction of per\-frame read advance removable while onset credit exists (0.0..1.0, default: 0.5). Accepts scalar or control file (.csv/.json).
  \-\-onset\-credit\-max ONSET_CREDIT_MAX
                        Maximum accumulated onset time credit in analysis\-frame units (default: 8.0). Accepts scalar or control file (.csv/.json).
  \-\-no\-onset\-realign    Disable fractional read\-position realignment on onsets when \-\-onset\-time\-credit is enabled.
  \-\-ambient\-preset      Convenience preset for ambient extreme stretch (random phase engine, onset\-time\-credit, transient preserve, conservative staging).
  \-\-auto\-segment\-seconds AUTO_SEGMENT_SECONDS
                        Optional segment size in seconds for long jobs. When >0, processing runs per segment with crossfade assembly.
  \-\-checkpoint\-dir CHECKPOINT_DIR
                        Directory used to cache per\-segment checkpoint chunks for resume workflows.
  \-\-checkpoint\-id CHECKPOINT_ID
                        Optional checkpoint run identifier (default: hash of input/settings).
  \-\-resume              Reuse existing checkpoint chunks from \-\-checkpoint\-dir when available.
  \-\-interp {none,linear,nearest,cubic,polynomial}
                        Interpolation mode for time\-varying control signals loaded from CSV/JSON (default: linear).
  \-\-order ORDER         Polynomial order for \-\-interp polynomial (default: 3). Accepts any integer >= 1; effective fit degree is min(order, control_points\-1).
  \-\-pitch\-shift\-semitones, \-\-target\-pitch\-shift\-semitones, \-\-pitch, \-\-semitones PITCH_SHIFT_SEMITONES
                        Pitch shift in semitones (+12 is one octave up). Accepts scalar or control file (.csv/.json).
  \-\-pitch\-shift\-cents, \-\-cents PITCH_SHIFT_CENTS
                        Pitch shift in cents (+1200 is one octave up). Accepts scalar or control file (.csv/.json).
  \-\-pitch\-shift\-ratio, \-\-ratio PITCH_SHIFT_RATIO
                        Pitch ratio (>1 up, <1 down). Accepts decimals (1.5), integer ratios (3/2), expressions (2^(1/12)), or a control file (.csv/.json).
  \-\-target\-f0 TARGET_F0
                        Target fundamental frequency in Hz. Auto\-estimates source F0 per file.
  \-\-analysis\-channel {first,mix}
                        Channel strategy for F0 estimation with \-\-target\-f0 (default: mix)
  \-\-f0\-min F0_MIN       Minimum F0 search bound in Hz (default: 50)
  \-\-f0\-max F0_MAX       Maximum F0 search bound in Hz (default: 1000)
  \-\-pitch\-mode {standard,formant\-preserving}
                        Pitch mode: standard shift or formant\-preserving correction (default: standard)
  \-\-formant\-lifter FORMANT_LIFTER
                        Cepstral lifter cutoff for formant envelope extraction (default: 32). Accepts scalar or control file (.csv/.json).
  \-\-formant\-strength FORMANT_STRENGTH
                        Formant correction blend 0..1 when pitch mode is formant\-preserving (default: 1.0). Accepts scalar or control file (.csv/.json).
  \-\-formant\-max\-gain\-db FORMANT_MAX_GAIN_DB
                        Max per\-bin formant correction gain in dB (default: 12). Accepts scalar or control file (.csv/.json).
  \-\-pitch\-map PITCH_MAP
                        CSV control map for time\-varying stretch/pitch. Columns: start_sec,end_sec plus optional stretch,pitch_ratio/pitch_cents/pitch_semitones,confidence. Use '\-' to read from stdin.
  \-\-pitch\-map\-stdin     Read control\-map CSV from stdin.
  \-\-control\-stdin       Alias for \-\-pitch\-map\-stdin (canonical control\-bus CSV stdin path).
  \-\-route EXPR          Control\-bus routing expression for map rows. Repeat flag to chain routes. Syntax: target=source, target=const(v), target=inv(source), target=pow(source,exp), target=mul(source,factor), target=add(source,offset), target=affine(source,scale,bias), target=clip(source,lo,hi). Targets: stretch,pitch_ratio. Sources: any numeric column present in the control\-map CSV.
  \-\-pitch\-follow\-stdin  Shortcut for \-\-pitch\-map\-stdin (sidechain pitch\-follow workflows).
  \-\-pitch\-conf\-min PITCH_CONF_MIN
                        Minimum accepted map confidence (default: 0 disables gating).
  \-\-pitch\-lowconf\-mode {hold,unity,interp}
                        Low\-confidence map handling mode (default: hold).
  \-\-pitch\-map\-smooth\-ms PITCH_MAP_SMOOTH_MS
                        Moving\-average smoothing over map pitch ratios in milliseconds.
  \-\-pitch\-map\-crossfade\-ms PITCH_MAP_CROSSFADE_MS
                        Crossfade between processed map segments in milliseconds (default: 8.0).

Transients:
  \-\-transient\-mode {off,reset,hybrid,wsola}
                        Transient handling mode: off (none), reset (phase reset), hybrid (PV steady + WSOLA transients), or wsola (time\-domain transient\-safe path).
  \-\-transient\-sensitivity TRANSIENT_SENSITIVITY
                        Transient detector sensitivity in [0,1] (higher catches more onsets). Accepts scalar or control file (.csv/.json).
  \-\-transient\-protect\-ms TRANSIENT_PROTECT_MS
                        Transient protection width in milliseconds (default: 30). Accepts scalar or control file (.csv/.json).
  \-\-transient\-crossfade\-ms TRANSIENT_CROSSFADE_MS
                        Crossfade duration for transient/steady stitching (default: 10 ms). Accepts scalar or control file (.csv/.json).

Stereo:
  \-\-stereo\-mode {independent,mid_side_lock,ref_channel_lock}
                        Channel coherence strategy: independent (legacy), mid_side_lock (M/S\-coupled), ref_channel_lock (phase\-lock to reference channel).
  \-\-ref\-channel REF_CHANNEL
                        Reference channel index used by \-\-stereo\-mode ref_channel_lock (default: 0).
  \-\-coherence\-strength COHERENCE_STRENGTH
                        Coherence lock strength in [0,1] (0=off, 1=full lock). Accepts scalar or control file (.csv/.json).

Output/Mastering:
  \-\-target\-sample\-rate TARGET_SAMPLE_RATE
                        Output sample rate in Hz (default: keep input rate)
  \-\-resample\-mode {auto,fft,linear}
                        Resampling engine (auto=fft if scipy available, else linear)
  \-\-normalize {none,peak,rms}
                        Output normalization mode
  \-\-peak\-dbfs PEAK_DBFS
                        Target peak dBFS when \-\-normalize peak
  \-\-rms\-dbfs RMS_DBFS   Target RMS dBFS when \-\-normalize rms
  \-\-target\-lufs TARGET_LUFS
                        Integrated loudness target in LUFS
  \-\-compressor\-threshold\-db COMPRESSOR_THRESHOLD_DB
                        Enable compressor above threshold dBFS
  \-\-compressor\-ratio COMPRESSOR_RATIO
                        Compressor ratio (>=1)
  \-\-compressor\-attack\-ms COMPRESSOR_ATTACK_MS
                        Compressor attack time in ms
  \-\-compressor\-release\-ms COMPRESSOR_RELEASE_MS
                        Compressor release time in ms
  \-\-compressor\-makeup\-db COMPRESSOR_MAKEUP_DB
                        Compressor makeup gain in dB
  \-\-expander\-threshold\-db EXPANDER_THRESHOLD_DB
                        Enable downward expander below threshold dBFS
  \-\-expander\-ratio EXPANDER_RATIO
                        Expander ratio (>=1)
  \-\-expander\-attack\-ms EXPANDER_ATTACK_MS
                        Expander attack time in ms
  \-\-expander\-release\-ms EXPANDER_RELEASE_MS
                        Expander release time in ms
  \-\-compander\-threshold\-db COMPANDER_THRESHOLD_DB
                        Enable compander threshold in dBFS
  \-\-compander\-compress\-ratio COMPANDER_COMPRESS_RATIO
                        Compander compression ratio (>=1)
  \-\-compander\-expand\-ratio COMPANDER_EXPAND_RATIO
                        Compander expansion ratio (>=1)
  \-\-compander\-attack\-ms COMPANDER_ATTACK_MS
                        Compander attack time in ms
  \-\-compander\-release\-ms COMPANDER_RELEASE_MS
                        Compander release time in ms
  \-\-compander\-makeup\-db COMPANDER_MAKEUP_DB
                        Compander makeup gain in dB
  \-\-limiter\-threshold LIMITER_THRESHOLD
                        Peak limiter threshold in linear full\-scale
  \-\-soft\-clip\-level SOFT_CLIP_LEVEL
                        Soft clip output ceiling in linear full\-scale
  \-\-soft\-clip\-type {tanh,arctan,cubic}
                        Soft clip transfer type
  \-\-soft\-clip\-drive SOFT_CLIP_DRIVE
                        Soft clip drive amount (>0)
  \-\-hard\-clip\-level HARD_CLIP_LEVEL
                        Hard clip level in linear full\-scale
  \-\-clip                Legacy alias: hard clip at +/\-1.0 when set
  \-\-manifest\-json MANIFEST_JSON
                        Write processing manifest JSON with per\-file settings and outcomes.
  \-\-manifest\-append     Append entries to an existing \-\-manifest\-json file instead of replacing it.
  \-\-subtype SUBTYPE     Explicit libsndfile output subtype override (e.g., PCM_16, PCM_24, FLOAT)
  \-\-bit\-depth {inherit,16,24,32f}
                        Output bit\-depth policy (default: inherit). Ignored when \-\-subtype is set.
  \-\-dither {none,tpdf}  Dither policy before quantized writes (default: none)
  \-\-dither\-seed DITHER_SEED
                        Deterministic RNG seed for dithering (default: random seed)
  \-\-true\-peak\-max\-dbtp TRUE_PEAK_MAX_DBTP
                        Apply output gain trim to enforce max true\-peak in dBTP
  \-\-metadata\-policy {none,sidecar,copy}
                        Output metadata policy: none, sidecar, or copy (sidecar implementation)

Beginner examples:
  pvx voc input.wav \-\-stretch 1.2 \-\-output output.wav
  pvx voc vocal.wav \-\-preset vocal \-\-pitch \-2 \-\-output vocal_tuned.wav
  pvx voc speech.wav \-\-transient\-mode hybrid \-\-stretch 1.25 \-\-output speech_hybrid.wav
  pvx voc stereo.wav \-\-stereo\-mode mid_side_lock \-\-coherence\-strength 0.9 \-\-stretch 1.2 \-\-output stereo_lock.wav
  pvx pitch\-track A.wav \-\-emit pitch_to_stretch \-\-output \- | pvx voc B.wav \-\-control\-stdin \-\-output B_follow.wav
  pvx voc input.wav \-\-stretch controls/stretch.csv \-\-interp linear \-\-output output.wav
  pvx voc input.wav \-\-example all
.fi
